From 4b18d3e7c0809b15e017623881f4c8734c450327 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shadatul Sofia <133907990+ShadatulSofia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 14:58:23 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Add admin Kandungan > Bahan oversight page
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Lists every teacher's material behind the same Subjek/Tahun filter as the video
list, with totals for all / PDF / DOCX / PPTX that follow the filter. Bahan is no
longer greyed out in the Kandungan menu.

Preview opens in a dialog, like the video list. PDFs and images show in place;
Word, PowerPoint and Excel cannot be rendered by a browser, so the dialog says so
and offers the download rather than faking a preview or handing the file to a
third-party viewer. Download is also its own action on every row.

DownloadController no longer counts a download when an admin opens the file. The
list shows download_count, so without this an audit would inflate the very number
it is auditing — the same reasoning that stops a teacher's own play counting as a
view (WatchController::markViewed).

Type counts match on original_name, since the extension is derived rather than
stored; the column collation is case-insensitive, so NOTA.PDF counts with the
rest. The Subjek/Tahun filter is now one shared helper across both lists.
